Summary:

“RK700, register your name.” Tony commands.

Then Tony mockingly bows at Steve with his right hand twirling before outstretched towards the android and takes a step back, “All yours captain.” Tony sung the words sarcastically, and Steve just rolls his eyes, but still appreciate that Tony let him name the android.

Steve didn’t have to, but he wanted to, and Tony knew that, because Tony knew exactly whose duplicate he made.

“Bucky.” Steve said to the Android.

The android smiled at his new owner, “My name is Bucky.”

Inspired by @umikochannart‘s dbh!Au STucky  and when i say inspired i mean I N S P I R E D, i can’t believe the ideas and beautiful crossovers that could be out of this GODDESS

summary: Young Justice 30 Day Challenge Day Fourteen
title: Young Justice 30 Day Challenge Day Fourteen
body:
14. Favorite From Justice League

Definitely Captain Marvel! Seriously, the way he wants to just hang out with the big kids is adorable. It kinda makes me sad that, before they knew he was only ten, The Team kinda shut him out more or less because they thought he was just a Leaguer who didn’t trust them and just wanted to babysit them. Like, the time he went to play fetch with Wolf waiting for The Team to come out in Humanity still breaks my heart every time I watch it. That and when he thought he would be invited to Miss Martian and Superboy’s school dance. Just makes you feel really sorry for the kid. I’m curious what they’ll do with his character this season since he’ll most likely be college age by now. I can see it now…

Batman: Captain Marvel, Klarion the Witch Boy is attempting to turn the entire city of New Orleans into a twisted, evil recreation of Candy Land. Full League response required.

Billy: Sorry, Bats. This psych class is kicking my butt. I need the night to study.

Batman: Billy, there are demon lollipops devouring Bourbon Street right now.

Billy: Yeah, cool. Hey, Batman, can you help me with this one question on my homework? It’s asking for an example of “negative reinforcement.” I don’t even remember hearing about that in class! Do you know what it means?

Batman: Billy, people are dying.

No, but seriously, though, that probably wouldn’t happen. Billy would totally drop his textbooks for the night and go help the League stop Klarion and his evil candy plot and would still manage to kick ass on his psych midterm. Dude’s just that awesome

summary: I feel this should have a trigger warning for anyone that has ever come home and found a guilty looking pet. At least in this...
caption:
I feel this should have a trigger warning for anyone that has ever come home and found a guilty looking pet. At least in this case, the furry duo have fought off some kind of interdimensional evil rather than having eaten Carol’s couch and then managed to spill the contents of the fridge everywhere (for example…), but damn, that still looks like some mess to clean up.

Another plus is that Rocket is no longer trying to kill Chewie, and that cat is actually something of an alien bad ass. So, sure, like most cats but with a little something extra. Carol should be glad she’s sticking around, as she might come in handy for something more than just kitty hugs

From Captain Marvel 8, by Kelly Sue DeConnick, Marcio Takara, Lee Loughridge & Joe Caramagna

summary: Do you see any parallels between Johann Schmidt and Kylo? I do. Schmidt 2as probably more pure evil at heart, but both were...
caption: Do you see any parallels between Johann Schmidt and Kylo? I do. Schmidt 2as probably more pure evil at heart, but both were brainwashed and seduced by the sheer amount of power they hoped to get by turning to the dark/evil side. They were exorbitantly ambitious and lead by their wish to become something bigger than life. And as I don’t consider Kylo a real fanatic of the First Order ideology, I wouldn’t say Schmidt was a real Nazi in all aspects of the ideology.

summary: Marvel Zombies RP Wanted Connection: Carol Danvers Requested by: Jessica Drew Telephone networks have failed, the internet is...
caption:
Marvel Zombies RP Wanted Connection: Carol Danvers
Requested by: Jessica Drew

Telephone networks have failed, the internet is gone. Modern communication seems to have come to an end. What remains is radiowaves. People with the right equipment have begun to communicate with anyone in range using CB radios, walkie talkies, whatever they can get their hands on. Some are broadcasting, some are just listening.

Carol slowly tuned through the channels on the old radio, she had crash landed on her reentry into the Earth’s atmosphere, and when she made it to Manhattan, the Tower was a wreckage. She heard the crackling sound of numbers coming through as she found an active channel –

This is Jessica Drew broadcasting for Carol Danvers. On the off chance you’re not in space and you’re out there, there’s somewhere safe. Haven. I’m here with Gerry. Clint is here. And Peter. Nat, Bobbi, Tony… I’ve saved you a room so you better get your ass here before someone steals it. Hope to see you soon! Love you, Kirk. Co-ordinates to follow…

Marvel Zombies RP is a Marvel Comics AU roleplay established 1 April 2017. We look forward to surviving with you.

Carol slowly tuned through the channels on the old radio, she had crash landed on her reentry into the Earth’s atmosphere, and when she made it to Manhattan, the Tower was a wreckage. She heard the crackling sound of numbers coming through as she found an active channel –

This is Jessica Drew broadcasting for Carol Danvers. On the off chance you’re not in space and you’re out there, there’s somewhere safe. Haven. I’m here with Gerry. Clint is here. And Peter. Nat, Bobbi, Tony… I’ve saved you a room so you better get your ass here before someone steals it. Hope to see you soon! Love you, Kirk. Co-ordinates to follow…
